FBIS4-47970 "drafr089_e_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-089 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 WEST AFRICA Mali U.S. Interests in Country Reportedly Threatened U.S. Interests in Country Reportedly Threatened AB0905083094 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1215 GMT 7 Apr 94 AB0905083094 Libreville Africa No. 1 French BFN [Text] In Mali, about 100 pupils and students yesterday attacked the premises of the French Development Fund in Bamako, the capital, destroying 11 vehicles and breaking the building's windows. The attack came a few days after the publication of a communique from an unknown armed resistance group, which has threatened to attack interests belonging to France, the United States, and Germany -- Mali's principal fund donors.
